[30;1m83 | [0m[35mEach time you call [`hikari.impl.buckets.RESTBucket.acquire`][] a request[0m
[30;1m84 | [0m[35mtimeslice for a given `Route`, several things happen. The first is that we[0m
[30;1m85 | [0m[35mattempt to find the existing bucket for that route, if there is one, or get an[0m
[30;1m86 | [0m[35munknown bucket otherwise. This is done by creating a real bucket hash from the[0m
[30;1m87 | [0m[35mcompiled route. The initial hash is calculated using a lookup table that maps[0m
[30;1m88 | [0m[35m`CompiledRoute` objects to their corresponding initial hash[0m
